<b>Clinical and Translational Card for Elranatamab</b>. 
<b>Mechanism of action</b>: BCMA&#x2010;CD3 bispecific antibody. 
<b>Indication</b>: Adult patients with triple&#x2010;class&#x2010;exposed relapsed/refractory multiple myeloma. 
<b>Dosage and administration</b>: The recommended subcutaneous elranatamab dosing consists of fixed step&#x2010;up doses of 12 mg on day 1 and 32 mg on day 4 followed by the full treatment dose of 76 mg once weekly (QW) from weeks 2 to 24. In responders, 76 mg QW is reduced to every 2&#x2009;weeks (Q2W) following &#x2265;&#x2009;6 cycles and to every 4&#x2009;weeks after &#x2265;&#x2009;6 Q2W cycles. 
<b>Major metabolic pathway</b>: Not applicable. 
<b>Key pharmacokinetic characteristics</b>: After the first subcutaneous elranatamab dose, <i>C</i>
<sub>max</sub> and AUC<sub>tau</sub> increased in a dose&#x2010;proportional manner over the evaluated dose range (&#x2248;6&#x2013;76 mg). The median <i>t</i>
<sub>max</sub> after the first dose across all dose levels was 7 (range, 3&#x2013;7) days. The <i>t</i>
